  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Gail Gordon, Lucille Ball's sidekick through radio and television, said
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   "the world will miss her greatly."
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   He said he will remember her as the best talent of her kind and a warm and wonderful friend.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   They first met in 1947 on her radio program "My Favorite Husband."
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   He joined her on television from 1962 to 1974.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   He last spoke with Miss Ball on his birthday in February.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   Gordon, 81,
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   performs in dinner theatres in Edmonton, Canada,
  </a>
  <a href="#9" id="9">
   and regrets that he will not be able to attend her funeral
  </a>
  <a href="#10" id="10">
   because of obligations to his current production.
  </a>
